f Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margarethe","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margarete Guistiniani was born about 1195, in Scala, Salerno, Campania, Italy, her father, Niccolo Giustiniani, was 6 and her mother, Marta D'Este, was 7. She married Jacopino Della Scala. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"ABT 1195–":"umbes 1195–Surnud","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","ABT 1195":"umbes 1195","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","Italy":"Itaalia","Scala, Salerno, Campania, Italy":"Scala, Salerno, Campania, Itaalia"},"fi":{"ABT 1195–":"noin 1195–Kuollut","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1190":"1190","ABT 1195":"noin 1195","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","Italy":"Italia","Scala, Salerno, Campania, Italy":"Scala, Salerno, Campania, Italia"},"fr":{"ABT 1195–":"environ 1195–Décédée","1195–Female":"1195–Décédée","1210–Male":"1210–Décédé","1230–Female":"1230–Décédée","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1190–Female":"1190–Décédée","1190":"1190","ABT 1195":"environ 1195","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","Italy":"Italie","Scala, Salerno, Campania, Italy":"Scala, Salerno, Campania, Italie","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Margarete Guist